<HEADLINE> Book Published on Jiang Zemin's Deeds in Party-Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A book recording the main
Party-building activities of Jiang Zemin, General Secretary of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, has been
published.
</P>
<P>
The book, titled "Chronology on General Secretary Jiang's
Important Deeds in Party-Building," can be referred to as a
historical record or a theoretical guidebook.
</P>
<P>
The main part of the book tells how the CPC Central Committee
with Jiang Zemin at the core has focused on Party-building and
important activities of the General Secretary from the Fourth
Plenary Session of the 13th CPC Central Committee to the First
Plenary Session of the 15th CPC Central Committee, showing Jiang's
main thinking and views on the Party's leadership and
Party-building.
</P>
<P>
The introduction summarizes his important viewpoints on
Party-building, while the appendix records the main achievements
in Party-building since the 14th CPC National Congress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
