<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Goes Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index dropped by 56.61 points on Wednesday to close at
1,434.61 points against Tuesday's close at 1,491.22 points.
</P>
<P>
A total trade volume of 131.04 million shares were traded
Wednesday as against 99.92 million the previous day.
</P>
<P>
The Karachi stock market took a nose-dive Wednesday as the news
of further Indian nuclear tests cast gloom in the market causing
punters to go into a selling spree.
</P>
<P>
The stock market plunged soon after the news of two more
nuclear tests carried out by India Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The market was already depressed. This Indian action has
driven away the foreign investors," said one trader.
</P>
<P>
Traders say they do not expect any recoveries in the stock
market until institutional and foreign investors return to the
trading floor.
</P>
<P>
"Currently, we are waiting to see how Pakistan reacts to the
Indian (nuclear) tests," said one trader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
