<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Concerned About India's Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kazakhstan Foreign Ministry
issued a statement on Wednesday to express its deep concern about
the underground nuclear tests in India.
</P>
<P>
India's action was against the principles of the Nuclear
Non-proliferation Treaty and the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty,
the statement said. The tests did great harm to the nuclear
disarmament and non-proliferation processes in the world.
</P>
<P>
The statement also stressed that India's tests aggravated
tensions in that region.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakhstan government proposed that India give up the
nuclear option to maintain world peace and stability and promote
international cooperation and development.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the Tajikistan government also issued a
statement to express its concern over India's nuclear
tests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
