<HEADLINE> Urgent: Clinton Imposes Economic Sanctions on India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
POTSDAM, Germany, May 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton announced here Wednesday that he had decided to impose
economic sanctions against India in protest against its nuclear
tests.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference after talks with German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl, Clinton described the nuclear tests conducted by India
as "unjustified" and "a terrible mistake", adding that "they clearly
create dangerous new instability in the region". 
</P>
</TEXT>
