<HEADLINE> Karpov Beats Chinese Women Chess Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- World chess champion Anatoly Karpov
outwitted his Chinese women players for three wins and one draw in
an exhibition competition here Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
With the absence of former woman world champion Xie Jun, four
other Chinese top women players failed to score a full point
against Karpov despite their intensive preparation and tough
attacks on the boards.
</P>
<P>
Among the four international grandmasters, only Wang Lei, who
played with the whites, managed for a draw while Wang Pin, Qin
Kaiying and Zhu Chen were all uprooted by the Russian world
champion.
</P>
<P>
Karpov said in a post-match interview that the competitions are
tough and full of fun, and he was challenged greatly in the
beginning of the all the four games before achieving winning
advantages in the last minutes.
</P>
<P>
Last August, Karpov played simultaneously against six Chinese
women players for four wins and two draws.
</P>
<P>
Under the schedule, Karpov will play four Chinese men players
on Friday in a 25-minute quickplay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
