</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- U.S. President Bill Clinton has planned to announce
economic sanctions against India Wednesday in Berlin for its
nuclear tests, U.S. officials said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Clinton had made up his mind about the sanctions during the
flight to Berlin where he arrived early Wednesday for a two-day
official visit, the officials said. (Clinton-India-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan applied economic sanctions against India on
Wednesday to protest against the South Asian nation's latest
testing of nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto said Tokyo would
suspend new grants-in-aid to India and shelve the plan to host a
meeting, scheduled for June 30 to July 1, of donor nations to
India. (Japan-India-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
