<HEADLINE> New Management System for Beijing's Mobile Telecom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mobile Telecom Bureau will
introduce a new software system as a solution for its mobile
telecommunications network from the U.S.-based Computer Associates
International Inc. An agreement was signed here today.
</P>
<P>
The Uni Centering system enables the display of all the
systems, sub-networks, applied programs and data banks in
Beijing's biggest mobile telecom network.
</P>
<P>
The bureau's exchanges have a total capacity of 1.35 million
ends with nearly 800,000 users, said bureau chief Zhang Jiaji,
adding that the capacity will be expanded to two million ends, and
the number of users will reach more than one million by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Computer Associates is the second biggest software company in
the United States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
