<DOCNO> XIE19980513.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mainland Scholars Complete Study of Common Law in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A reception was held Wednesday to
bid farewell to 10 law scholars and officials from China's
mainland who have completed their nine-month study in common law
at the University of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Andrew Li, chief justice of the Court of Final Appeal of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, presented souvenirs to
each of the 10 scholars at the reception held Wednesday evening in
the old Bank of China Building.
</P>
<P>
They were recruited from renowned universities and government
institutions, including the Legislative Affairs Commission of the
National People's Congress, the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office
of the State Council, the Center for the Training of Senior Judges
of the Supreme People's Court, and the Chinese University of
Political Science and Law.
</P>
<P>
Their study in Hong Kong was made possible under a scholarship
scheme for Chinese scholars in the interior areas to study common
law at the University of Hong Kong in the Postgraduate Diploma in
Common Law, which was launched last September.
</P>
<P>
The program, which aims at facilitating academic exchange
between scholars of law in Hong Kong and the mainland, enables law
teachers and lawyers from China's mainland to study the common law
of the Anglo-American world.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, Chen Yu Tian from the Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office said that through the nine-month study in Hong
Kong, he has had a general idea about Hong Kong's legal system.
</P>
<P>
"I have been deeply impressed by Hong Kong's rule of law and
have a better understanding of the community of Hong Kong," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Under the Basic Law, after Hong Kong returned to China on July
1, 1997, the judicial system previously practiced in Hong Kong
shall be maintained except for those changes consequent upon the
establishment of the Court of Final Appeal of the HKSAR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
