<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Basketballers Leave for World Meets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women basketball team
left here this afternoon for a five-member international meet in
the Czech Republic and the upcoming world championship in Germany.
</P>
<P>
The 19-member Chinese team will first play against the United
States, Canada, Australia and the Czech Republic in the friendly
tournament before leaving for Germany on May 22.
</P>
<P>
In the world championship to be started on May 26, China was
bracketed in Group A with Argentina, Russia and Spain, with top
three teams of the four groups advancing to the second round
round-robin two-group competition.
</P>
<P>
From the round-robin competitions, top four teams of each of
the two groups will advance to the quarterfinals. 
</P>
