<HEADLINE> Industrial Projects Win HK Government's Fund Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 47 industrial projects
will be financed by the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) Government's fund this year.
</P>
<P>
The Industrial Support Fund, established in 1994, aims to
support projects that can contribute to Hong Kong's industrial or
technology development.
</P>
<P>
The fund is granted on a yearly basis by the Industry and
Technology Development Council (ITDC). Over the past four years,
297 projects have won the financial support.
</P>
<P>
Annie Choi, secretary of ITDC, said that the 47 newly approved
projects would cost a total of 187 million HK dollars (24 million
U.S. dollars) in the next four years. These projects range from
biotechnology to information technology, electronics and metals,
and a half of the projects are carried out by higher educational
institutions. 
</P>
