<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index Down 30.9 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Stock Exchange index
slipped by 30.9 points Wednesday to close at 2,273.6 points
compared with 2,304.5 points at Tuesday's closing.
</P>
<P>
The volume, transactions and value all showed a decrease with a
total of 66.106 million shares being traded over 1,770 deals
compared with 85.662 million shares over 2,278 transactions
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The value of the shares changed hands also dropped to 18.568
million Kuwaiti dinars (61.274 million U.S. dollars) compared with
24.146 million Kuwaiti dinars (79.68 million U.S. dollars)
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The trading week ending Wednesday saw a decline of 2.7
percent, or 64.4 points from 2,338 points recorded last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The index of the first two days of the week kept a continuous
drop from 2,338 points to 2335.1 points and again to 2321.9
points, but it rebounded by 3.5 points Monday.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait stock exchange market, where 75 companies and mutual
funds are listed, powered ahead for two consecutive weeks ending
last Wednesday due to strong confidence in the new Kuwaiti
government's plans to boost the country's economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
