<HEADLINE> Hingis Enters Third Round in German Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis of Switzerland remained
unbeaten on clay this year, breezing past Romanian Silvia Farina
to reach the third round of the German Open on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The top-seeded Hingis needed 58 minutes to beat the veteran
6-0, 7-5 in 926,000 U.S. dollars event, which attracted 28 of the
world's top 30 players.
</P>
<P>
However, sixth seed Mary Pierce of France was forced to
withdraw with a strained left thigh while trailing against
Austrian Barbara Paulus 6-4, 6-7 (1-7), 1-3.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's Amanda Coetzer, ranked fourth, led three Top 10
players into the third round, edging Germny's Andrea Glass 6-0,
4-6, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Conchita Martinez, seeded No. 7, advanced by ousting
compatriot Magui Serna 6-2, 6-2, while No. 8 Irina Spirleas of
Romania won easily 6-4, 6-1 over American Meghann Shaughsy.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, who rolled into the tournament with a spotless 9-0
record on clay, played almost flawless tennis in closing out the
first set against the 26-year-old Farina in just 19 minutes.
</P>
