<HEADLINE> Indonesian Military Leader Appeals for Restraint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Defense Minister and
ABRI (Armed Forces) Commander Gen. Wiranto appealed Wednesday to
students and security officers to exercise self-restraint to avoid
further clashes that could claim more lives.
</P>
<P>
"Clashes are getting out of hand. All parties should think
clearly and constructively to maintain a peaceful atmosphere in
solving problems," the official Antara News Agency quoted the
general as saying.
</P>
