<HEADLINE> Interior Decoration Market Attractive to Overseas Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China's interior decoration market
has become increasingly attractive to overseas enterprises as
shown by a four-day exposition.
</P>
<P>
The 6th China International Construction, Interior Decoration
and Hotel Facility Expo and China International Construction
Ceramics, Tiles and Sanitary Ware Expo opened here today, and more
than 200 world manufacturers are attending.
</P>
<P>
Promoted by a thriving real estate industry, demand for
interior decoration is on the rise in China, and the annual total
output value for related projects amounts to 80 billion
yuan. Thirty billion yuan of which goes to interior decoration of
residential housing, 13 billion yuan to office buildings and
hotels, and 25 billion yuan to rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Some multinational corporations have reported good results in
China. Formica, the world's largest fire-resistant board producer,
for example, has seized 60 percent of China's market since the
U.S. firm started business in the country four years ago. 
</P>
