<HEADLINE> Ranariddh's Generals Back For Reintegration Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of resistance
generals loyal to deposed First Prime Minister Prince Norodom
Ranariddh arrived here Wednesday for talks on re-integrating their
forces into the Royal Cambodian Armed Forces (RCAF).
</P>
<P>
This was the first return of the five-member group, led by
resistance commander Khann Savoeun, to Phnom Penh since last July.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh and his forces have been in exile since last July in
the wake of the ousting of the prince, then first prime minister,
by his co-premier, Hun Sen, in a military clash.
</P>
<P>
The exact date for the start of the talks has not yet been
announced.
</P>
<P>
Prince Ranariddh agreed, in an April 17 statement, to transfer
zones controlled by his forces and order integration of his forces
into the RCAF.
</P>
<P>
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen appointed his five officials to
meet and discuss with General Khann Savoeun on May 4.
</P>
<P>
This discussion was the last step in the last requirement of a
peace plan brokered by Japan, which paid the way for Ranariddh to
participate in the July 26 elections, Hun Sen's cabinet said.
</P>
<P>
Resistance commander Nhiek bun Chhay said his team would make
five proposals, including a cease-fire and amnesty for royalist
officers convicted on criminal charges with Prince Ranariddh
earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The other demands were the return of old ranks for royalist
officers, the return of property and a guarantee of protection
from the United Nations and the Phnom Penh government. 
</P>
