<HEADLINE> Australia Calls on Pakistan to Step off Nuclear Path </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Australia Wednesday called on
Pakistan to adopt the high moral ground and not respond to Indian
nuclear tests by developing its own weapons.
</P>
<P>
Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer said he conveyed
that message to Pakistan's High Commissioner Khawar Zaman during
a meeting in Canberra Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"I wanted to make it clear to him personally, not just through
my officials, that it would be a matter of very great concern if
Pakistan were to follow India and detonate a nuclear device," he
told journalists here.
</P>
<P>
"It is the Australian Government's view that Pakistan should
take the high moral ground, should not make the mistake of
detonating any type of nuclear device, and ensure that Pakistan
doesn't contribute to the proliferation of nuclear weapons."
</P>
<P>
Downer said Zaman promised to convey Australia's views to his
government.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the foreign minister said "the Australian
government strongly condemns" India's nuclear tests, and recalled
Australian High Commissioner to India, Rob Laurie, for
consultations. 
</P>
