<HEADLINE> Chi Haotian Meets Chief of Staff of Indonesian Air Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The development of multi-level and
all-around friendly and cooperative ties between the armed forces
of China and Indonesia is not only in the interests of the two
peoples, but also conducive to peace in the region and the world
at large General Chi Haotian said today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark in a meeting with General Acm Tubagus, chief
of staff of the Indonesian Air Force.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
state councillor and defence minister, noted that China and
Indonesia have been good neighbors since ancient time and are
among the countries that initiated the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-existence. The two countries share many similarities, he said.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries have developed smoothly
since the resumption of diplomatic ties, he said, adding that the
frequent exchanges of high-level visits have promoted mutual
understanding and friendship and advanced bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the financial turmoil in Southeast Asia, Chi
said that China supports the policies and measures adopted by the
Indonesian government to recover its economy and that China will
do its utmost to contribute to the solution of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that relations between the two armed forces have
enjoyed stable growth in conjunction with the development of
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that Tubagus' visit to China will play
a positive role in pushing forward the friendly and cooperative
ties between the two armed forces, especially the two air forces.
</P>
<P>
Tubagus said that his visit to China is aimed at increasing the
friendly and cooperative ties between the two armed forces,
especially the two air forces.
</P>
<P>
He added that he had very good talks with Lieutenant Liu
Shunyao, commander of the Air Force of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA), and that a consensus on many issues has
been reached between them.
</P>
<P>
He expressed thanks to the Chinese government for its
assistance to Indonesia during the financial crisis that swept
Southeast Asia, adding that with full support of friends,
Indonesia will extricate itself out of difficulties at an earlier
time.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Liu Shunyao was present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tubagus arrived here on Tuesday for a four-day official visit
to China as Liu's guest.  
</P>
</TEXT>
