<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Ends Conference on Taiwan Affairs (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A three-day working conference on
Taiwan affairs of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist
Party (CPC) ended here today. The committee called for more
efforts to create favorable conditions for China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
delivered a keynote address at the conference, whose participants
included other members of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee: Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li
Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
With the return of Hong Kong followed by Macao, the settlement
of the Taiwan issue and its ultimate reunification with the
motherland are desired by the whole nation, including Taiwan
compatriots, as well as a paramount historical mission of both the
Party and the nation, according to the conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference called on the whole Party and the nation to
further implement the principles of "peaceful reunification" and
"one country, two systems" and Jiang Zemin's eight-point proposal
for promoting China's reunification as well as the proper
management of all work in handling Taiwan affairs.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier and Member of the Political Bureau of the
CPC Central Committee Qian Qichen also delivered an important
speech during the conference. Chen Yunlin, director of the Taiwan
Affairs offices of the CPC Central Committee and the State
Council, also presented a work report.
</P>
<P>
Since the CPC Central Committee held its working conference on
Taiwan affairs in 1990, great changes have taken place in Taiwan's
situation and cross-straits relations, according to the conference.
</P>
<P>
Under the principles of "peaceful reunification" and "one
country, two systems," severe and complicated campaigns were
launched to fight against the separatist forces on the island and
anti-China forces in the world community, according to the
conference.
</P>
<P>
However, the unofficial trade and economic cooperation as well
as cultural and personnel exchanges have increased significantly
and these activities have greatly promoted mutual understanding
and national emotions among people on both sides of the Straits.
</P>
<P>
The smooth return of Hong Kong last July and the successful
implementation of the "one country, two systems" principle would
surely give an impetus to cross-straits relations and set an
example for the ultimate resolution of the Taiwan issue, the
conference reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980513.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Ends Conference on Taiwan Affairs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference called on all Party members to carry out the
guidelines of the 15th National Congress, hold high the banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory, focus on boosting the national economy, and
-- on this basis -- promote the overall development of
cross-straits relations and create favorable conditions for the
full resolution of the Taiwan question.
</P>
<P>
Party members should adhere to the basic principle of "peaceful
reunification" and "one country, two systems" and the eight-point
proposal put forward by Jiang Zemin, and make a firm stand against
any attempts to split Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Party members should also continue to push ahead economic,
cultural, sports, educational, scientific, technological and
personnel exchanges between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Active steps should be made to hold cross-straits political
talks under the principle of "one China" to end the state of
hostility between the two sides as early as possible, the
committee said. In this sense, procedural talks can be conducted
first about the topics and places for formal talks, according to
the conference.
</P>
<P>
The committee expects the Taiwan authorities to give up its
separatist advocacy and enter political talks as soon as possible
by proceeding from the overall interests of the Chinese nation and
the long-term interests of compatriots in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the motherland's reunification, the conference
pinned hopes on compatriots in Taiwan who have the fine tradition
of patriotism and have made great contributions to boosting
cross-straits relations.
</P>
<P>
To achieve peaceful reunification in accordance with the
principle of "one country, two systems" meets Taiwan people's
aspiration for peace, stability and maintaining the current
situation, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
Party members should strive to carry out the principle of
relying on people in Taiwan, have a better understanding of their
thinking, fully take their interests into consideration and
respect their aspirations, they said.
</P>
<P>
Policies and regulations concerning Taiwan should be improved
and formalities for Taiwan people's entry to the mainland
should be simplified so that the compatriots in Taiwan will find
it more convenient to travel, visit relatives, expand business and
study in the mainland areas of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
During the critical period at the turn of a new century, the
country's reunification and national revitalization will be
historical tides which cannot be resisted, they said.
</P>
<P>
The work related to Taiwan is a key matter of the Party and the
whole country, and more people should be united and all positive
factors should be mobilized to strengthen the work, according to
the conference.
</P>
<P>
Various departments should follow the unified arrangements of
the CPC Central Committee and make concerted efforts so as to do
the work well, they said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, all patriotic people should unite and work
hard for the peaceful reunification of the motherland and the
revitalization of the Chinese nation, according to the
conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
