<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- American International
Underwriters (AIU), runaway winners of the 1997 Hong Kong
Corporate Golf League, will be the first ever team to represent
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) at the second
World Corporate Golf Challenge, it was announced here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The World Corporate Golf Challenge is scheduled for May 18-20
at Hyatt La Manga Club Resort in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Captained by Ross Matthews, President of AIU Hong Kong &AMP; China,
AIU will tee-off against corporate golf champions from 20
countries and regions in the two-day, 36-hole 3/4 handicap
Stableford tournament.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian engineering company Ciri Juara Sdn. Bhd. won the
inaugural tournament at the same venue in 1997, with a total of
174 points, and the runners-up Jaguar of England were nine points
behind.
</P>
<P>
The World Corporate Golf Challenge is expected to be the
world's largest golf event with over 200,000 players from 36
countries and regions competing for the chance to represent their
countries and regions in the 1999 tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR is to launch the local Corporate Golf
Challenge event in June this year. The organizers are soon to
invite companies to enter their teams at the local event to find
the next Hong Kong Corporate Golf Challenge champions. 
</P>
