<HEADLINE> Entry Visa for Cambodia Required </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Cambodian government has
required all foreign travelers except those holding valid
passports of the countries or territories that have visa exemption
agreements with Cambodia to apply for entry visa prior to their
departure to the country.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
Government said the Cambodian government had notified the
Immigration Department of Hong Kong of the requirement, which will
be effective from May 15.
</P>
<P>
As Hong Kong has not entered into any visa exemption agreements
with Cambodia, Hong Kong residents will need to obtain a visa
from the Cambodian Consulate in Hong Kong before their departure
to Cambodia, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Previously, foreign travelers to Cambodia can obtain entry visa
upon arrival at the Pochengtong International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Appropriate entry visas can be obtained at the nearest
Cambodian embassies or consulates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
