<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Dong Well in Attracting FDI: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China has been doing quite well
this year in terms of attracting foreign direct investment (FDI),
a senior Chinese official said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the first four months this year, the contracted value of
FDI reached 13.56 billion U.S. dollars, up 12.24 percent compared
with a year earlier, according to Ma Xiuhong, director-general of
Foreign Investment Administration of the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Actually utilized value of FDI totaled 11.72 billion U.S.
dollars during the period, up a minor 0.07 percent from a year
ago," she added.
</P>
<P>
However, the number of foreign-financed projects approved
dipped 6.84 percent to 5,704, the official pointed out.
</P>
<P>
She was here attending a press conference prior to the '98
China Investment Policy Seminar, which is to be held here in early
 June in conjunction with the '98 China (Hong Kong) Investment
Symposium.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese official noted that in the first four months of
this year, the nation's economic development was healthy and
stable, with GDP growing by 7.9 percent and inflation dropping by
1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although adversely affected by the regional financial turmoil,
China's external trade achieved satisfactory results, she said,
adding "The volume of external trade amounted to 97.4 billion U.S.
dollars in the first four months, up 7.96 percent over the
previous year while exports gaining 11.73 percent to hit 56.18
billion U.S. dollars."
</P>
<P>
"China will make continued efforts to improve its investment
environment and enhance foreign investors' confidence in China,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, the contracted value of FDI flowing
into China totaled 534.7 billion U.S. dollars and the actually
utilized FDI is 233.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
China has for the past several years ranked second, only after
the United States, in attracting FDI. 
</P>
</TEXT>
