<HEADLINE> Japan's Nakata Wins Asian Player of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Japan's midfielder Hidetoshi
Nakata was honored on Wednesday the Asian Player of the Year by
the Asian Football Confederation.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Nakata, 21, became the youngest winner of the award in
its four-year history.
</P>
<P>
Nakata, who also won Japan's Player of the Year title, was
given the award after his performances in the World Cup qualifying
competitions where he played a pivotal role in the Asia' third
place play-off against Iran.
</P>
<P>
The confederation's Young Player of the Year award went to
Iranian Mehdi Mahdavikia, of Tehran's top club Piruzi.
</P>
<P>
Mahdavikia burst on to the international scene last year during
the World Cup qualifiers as Iran, who won the National Team of the
Year award, qualified for their first World Cup finals in 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Cha Bum-kun won the Coach of the Year award after leading South
Korea to its fourth successive World Cup finals and Saudi Arabia's
Al Hilal was named Club of the Year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
