<HEADLINE> Chinese Minister of Justice Meets Former U.S. State Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Justice Gao
Changli said today that China is ready to increase judicial
exchanges with the United States and other countries, particularly
cooperation in lawyers' affair area.
</P>
<P>
Gao made the remark in a meeting with former U.S. State
Secretary Warren Christopher, who is here as the guest of the
Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Gao said that the two countries have exhibited a good
momentum of cooperation in lawyers' affairs.
</P>
<P>
Lawyers' offices in the US and other countries have set up more
than 60 offices across China.
</P>
<P>
Christopher said that the two countries share much in common in
judicial cooperation, and he expressed the hope that bilateral
cooperation in lawyer affairs will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
Christopher, who serves as a senior partner of O'Melveny &AMP;
Myers LLP, will travel to Shanghai for events organized by
the Shanghai Branch of O'Melveny &AMP; Myers LLP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
