<HEADLINE> New Chinese Ambassador on Friendly Sino-Brunei Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese ambassador
extraordinary and plenipotentiary Wang Jianli Wednesday presented
his credentials to Brunei Darussalam Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah in
Brunei's capital Bandar Seri Begawan.
</P>
<P>
During the cordial and friendly conversation with the Sultan
after the presentation, the new Chinese ambassador conveyed
cordial greetings from Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Chinese
Premier Zhu Rongji to the Sultan, a spokesman of the Chinese
embassy in Bandar Seri Begawan told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Wang spoke highly of the great achievements made by the Brunei
government in the diversified economic development and improving
the living standard of its people.
</P>
<P>
Wang also appreciated the increasingly important role being
played by Brunei in the regional and international affairs and the
positive contributions made by the Brunei government to help
Southeast Asian countries overcome the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Wang said the Chinese government attaches importance to the
friendly relationship with Brunei and expressed his belief that
with the joint efforts, the friendly cooperation between China and
Brunei will have a steady development.
</P>
<P>
The Brunei Sultan who thanked the Chinese president and the
Chinese premier for their warm greetings and requested the Chinese
ambassador to convey his greetings to them.
</P>
<P>
Bolkiah recalled his state visit to China in 1993, which he
said promoted the development of the bilateral friendly relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that he would have more chances to meet Chinese
leaders and that there would be more Brunei government officials
to visit China in the years to come to further strengthen the
bilateral cooperative relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
