<HEADLINE> Harlem Brundtland Elected New WHO Director-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Gro Harlem Brundtland was elected
the new director-general of the World Health Organization (WHO)
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 59-year-old former Norwegian prime minister was formally
elected at the plenary session of the 51st World Health Assembly,
WHO's highest governing body.
</P>
<P>
She was nominated as director-general by the WHO Executive
Board last January.
</P>
<P>
Ms Brundtland will not assume office until July when her
predecessor Hiroshi Nakajima leaves the post which he has been
holding for 10 years.
</P>
<P>
As a medical doctor and Master of Public Health, Ms Brundtland
spend 10 years as physician and scientist in her country's public
health system.
</P>
<P>
For more than 20 years she was in public office, 10 of them as
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Throughout her political career, Ms Brundtland has developed a
growing concern for issues of global significance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
