<HEADLINE> Education Base to Train Economics Professionals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Education will set up
a base to train professionals in the field of economics, according
to a national education work conference held recently in this
capital city of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
An educational official said that the establishment of the base
is to develop research on basic theory of economics.
</P>
<P>
The base will start enrollment this summer for college
students who majored in sciences.
</P>
<P>
Over the past seven years, China has set up 84 training bases
of basic sciences and 51 training bases of liberal arts with
the aim of training various kinds of professional researchers and
lecturers.
</P>
<P>
A large number of students graduated from the bases have been
playing an important role in the country's educational and
scientific research. 
