<HEADLINE> Japan's Upper House Against India's Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Japan's House of Councillors, or the
upper house of parliament, adopted Wednesday a resolution to
protest against India's nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session, the upper house agreed to ask the
Japanese government to protest India's explosion of three nuclear
devices Monday and to take appropriate measures.
</P>
<P>
Saying India's underground testing is in defiance of
international efforts under the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, the
resolution urged India to immediately halt nuclear development.
</P>
<P>
Responding to the resolution, Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto said his government will do its best to persuade India
to halt its nuclear experiments and nuclear weapons development.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto called on all countries concerned to exercise the
utmost restraint so the stability of the region is not affected.
</P>
</TEXT>
