<HEADLINE> 4 Bidders Picked for Uganda Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Four companies have been chosen by
Uganda's Privatization Unit (PU) to bid for the purchase of a big
portion of shares in Uganda Airlines.
</P>
<P>
They are British Airways, Sabena Airways, Air Mauritius,
Alliance Air/South African Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Micheal Opagi, the PU director, said strict criteria would
be applied to select a strategic investor and that the
divestiture program of the parastatal is expected to be completed
by September.
</P>
<P>
The selling of the airline was fiercely protested by the
airlines staff as most of them would be laid off as a result of
the sale. They vented out complaints in spite of promised
terminal benefits.
</P>
<P>
Opagi warned that personal grudges should not interfere with
the divestiture process of the airline, adding that the
government is looking for a competent investor who will be able
to develop Entebbe into a regional air transport hub.
</P>
<P>
Uganda Airlines is based in Entebbe, 45 km south of Kampala,
and has more than three hundred staff members and two planes. It
has performed badly due to economic problems and shrinking market
share caused by coming of powerful foreign competitors. 
</P>
