<HEADLINE> Technical Improvements Help China's Copper Smelting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Production capacity at China's
largest copper smelting plant is now 150,000 tons of electrolytic
copper, an increase of 40,000 tons in a two-year period, thanks to
technical improvements, a Jiangxi Copper Industry Corp. official
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The output is expected to reach 200,000 tons by the year
2000, when the second phase of the technical improvement project
is completed. By then, the company will be one of the top 17 in
the world.
</P>
<P>
The equipment now in use went into operation in 1986 at the
Guixi Smelting Plant, one of the company's branches, then the
first phase of technical improvements began in 1992, bringing the
production capacity to 100,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
