<HEADLINE> Arab Man Stabbed to Death in Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 13 (Xinhua) - An Arab man was stabbed to death
in a northern Jerusalem neighborhood Wednesday morning by a
suspected Jewish extremist, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place on the corner of Hanavim and Shivtel
Israel streets in the Bet Israel neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
Large forces of Israeli police were deployed in the area to
search for the assailant believed to be Jewish, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The incident was the sixth stabbing of Arabs in the same area
in the past months.
</P>
<P>
Police said that they believed the series of attacks were
carried out by the same man out of nationalistic motivation.
</P>
<P>
They suspected the assailant was also responsible for setting
up explosive devices outside the apartment rented by three Arab
students in the nearby Mea Shearim neighborhood for a few months.
</P>
<P>
There has been a surge of terror attacks by both Jewish and
Arab extremists in Jerusalem at a time when the
Israeli-Palestinian peace process is deeply deadlocked.
</P>
<P>
A Jewish religious student was stabbed to death by suspected
Arab extremist in East Jerusalem last Wednesday. In another
similar attack last February, a 30-year-old Jewish student was
killed on his way to a synagogue also in East Jerusalem.
</P>
</TEXT>
