<HEADLINE> U.S. Firm Unveils New Digital Copiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Xerox Corp., of the United
States, unveiled Tuesday a pair of new digital copiers that are
25-30 percent cheaper than comparable old-style copiers.
</P>
<P>
Initial list prices, as quoted by the company, are 2,095
U.S. dollars for Xerox 212, a 12-page-per-minute model, and 2,550
dollars for Xerox 214, a 14-page-per-minute version.
</P>
<P>
Xerox "is breaking some ground" by bringing out a digital
machine less expensive than competing analog ones, said industry
consultant Barry Tepper with CAP Ventures Inc.
</P>
<P>
A few years ago, Tepper said, digital copiers were 50-80
percent more expensive than their analog competitors.
</P>
<P>
Xerox drove down production costs for the machines by using
premanufactured kits from four outside suppliers.
</P>
<P>
Digital equipment now makes up nearly 40 percent of Xerox's 18
billion dollars revenues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
