<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Friendship Conference in Northwestern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The 12th conference of the 21st
Century Committee for Sino-Japanese Friendship opened in Xi'an,
the capital of China's Shaanxi Province today.
</P>
<P>
China's Premier Zhu Rongji sent a letter to the conference,
saying that establishing long-term and stable good-neighborly
relations with Japan is in the fundamental interest of the two
countries and their peoples and conducive to the peace and the
development of the Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 20th anniversary of the China-Japan Peace
and Friendship Treaty. President Jiang Zemin will visit Japan this
fall, Zhu said, so the conference and its exploring the
development of bilateral relations comes at a critical moment and
is very significant.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto, who also sent a
letter, said that the two countries' leaders have exchanged
frequent visits since last year, and this has helped deepen mutual
understanding and bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that both sides will seize this
opportunity and consider bilateral relations from a long-term
perspective.
</P>
<P>
Participants are expected to discuss bilateral co-operation in
the economy, trade, and science and technology. 
</P>
