<HEADLINE> Kenya Calls for Better Agricultural Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Agriculture Minister
Musalia Mudavadi has called for better agricultural performance
to speed up overall economic growth in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government has already taken policies aimed at
enhancing the performance of the agricultural sector as the
engine of economic growth, the Daily Nation newspaper Wednesday
quoted the agriculture minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting on "Strategies for Raising Productivity
in Agriculture" on Tuesday, Mudavadi noted that agricultural
growth is a prerequisite for industrial and overall economic
growth in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Given our current state of economic depression and widespread
poverty, any measure that spurs economic growth and reduction of
poverty is most desirable," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that all the agricultural subsectors, with
the exception of tea and horticulture, have been recording a
steady decline due to poor planning and ineffective
implementation of government policies.
</P>
<P>
While agricultural performance has fluctuated over the years,
particularly since the beginning of the 1990s, population growth
has maintained an upward trend, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the current situation implied there was a
deterioration of food security and increased poverty. To avoid
this situation, the minister called for doubled efforts for the
Kenyans to ensure sustained agricutural growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
