<HEADLINE> China, Japan to Host Seminar on Textiles In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan will jointly host a
seminar on textiles quality and management this July in Shanghai,
China's largest commercial center.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and Japanese experts will discuss quality management
system and operation of Japan's textiles, quality demand for
textiles in Japanese market and situation of China's textiles on
the seminar, which will be sponsored by China Chamber of Commerce
for Import and Export of Textiles(CCCT) and Japan Textiles
Importers Association.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Japanese textiles trade holds an important position in
China's textiles trade, with the trade volume of textiles between
the two countries reaching 12.49 billion US dollars, accounting
for 20.7 percent of China's total textile import and export.
</P>
<P>
There remains some major problems in bilateral textiles trade,
namely, the proportion of processing trade dominates two thirds of
 China's total export of textiles to Japan.
</P>
<P>
China's advantages in low cost has reduced gradually due to the
impact of financial crisis in southeast Asia, besides, Chinese
enterprises should learn more about Japanese market.
</P>
<P>
Chinese textiles enterprises must enhance the sense of textiles
quality, develop high value-added products and create its own
name-brand products, according to CCCT Vice-Chairman Zhang
Guotian. 
</P>
</TEXT>
