<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
drifted lower on Wednesday, affected by the weaker Asian markets
and higher short-term interest rates at home.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 3 points lower at 2229 with a turnover
of nearly 202 million N.Z. dollars (108 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Trading in Lion Nathan shares accounted for half of the total
turnover, and the shares rose 2 cents to 460 cents. Also higher
were Fletcher Energy, climbing 10 cents to 653 cents, and Telecom,
gaining 3 cents to 850 cents.
</P>
<P>
On the decline side, Air New Zealand lost 2 cents to 204 cents,
Brierley Investment eased 1 cent to 100 cents, Carter Holt Harvey
lost 5 cents to 227 cents, and Fletcher Building dipped 4 cents to
319 cents.
</P>
<P>
The overall tone was weaker with 38 rises against 49 falls.
</P>
</TEXT>
