<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Township Enterprises Eye Foreign Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The township enterprises in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong province, have been
successful in introducing foreign capital over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the township enterprises completed 26.15
billion U.S. dollars worth imports and exports last year, up
22.25 percent from the year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
According to an official of the Guangzhou Administrative Bureau
of Rural and Township Enterprises, the foreign capital, mainly from
Europe, the United States and Japan, has been used to develop
products with high added-values and involving high technologies.
</P>
<P>
The Baiyun Weigao Motorcycle Co., for example, has recently
reached an agreement with a big Japanese company to jointly
manufacture motorcycles. Meanwhile, the Baiyun Electric Appliances
Group has introduced 30 million U.S. dollars from Germany to
produce new-model high- and low-pressure switches and half of the
products will be sold in Germany. Plus, the Fanyu Wanding (Group)
Co. has decided to cooperate with some northern European countries
to produce machinery for environment protection.
</P>
<P>
As part of the effort to upgrade the township enterprises, 12
township enterprises in Guangzhou have been approved to do import
and export independently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
