<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Developing Steadily in South China's City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Zhuhai, one of China's five Special
Economic Zones (SEZ) in Guangdong province got 1.67 billion US
dollars of total imports and exports in the first four months this
year, a rise of 11.1 percent over the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
An official from the city government said that Zhuhai SEZ took
efforts to increase exports and imports by developing investment
environment, granting more autonomy to export businesses and
simplifying investment procedures.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Zhuhai utilized 1.02 billion US dollars of foreign
investment, up 12.8 percent on the previous year. It achieved
total imports and exports of 5.52 billion US dollars, up 11.6
percent on that of 1996, with approximately three billion US
dollars of exports, an increase of 20.4 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the official noted, the total exports and imports of
Zhuhai are expected to reach over 6 billion US dollars this year,
with 3.4 billion US dollars of exports, and 1.046 billion US
dollars of foreign investment to be put to use.  
</P>
