<HEADLINE> 4 Palestinians Killed, 22 Wounded in Israeli Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Four palestinians were killed and 22
others wounded early Wednesday morning in eastern Lebanese
province of Bekaa in an Israeli air raid, Lebanon's NAN radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
The heavy casualties were caused when Israeli airplanes
blasted positions of Palestinian Fatah Movement and Popular Front
for the Liberation of Palestinian-General Command in Diera Taniye
area, central part of Bekaa.
</P>
<P>
Following the attack, the radio said, the wounded, one
seriously, were rushed to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
It is unknown why Israeli troops launched the attack on
Palestinians, who are now living as refugees in Lebanon, after
Israeli soldiers were wounded by Katyusha attacks launched by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah fired Katyusha missiles onto Israeli territory on
Monday night, wounding two Israeli soldiers in its northern area
of Galilee. This is the first casualties of Israelis on Israeli
territory in more than two years.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel occupied a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip in
south Lebanon in 1985, Lebanon's resistance, spearheaded by
Hezbollah, has been engaged in a guerrilla war trying to drive the
2,000 Israeli occupying troops from south Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
