<HEADLINE> Auto City in Northeast China Striving to Attract More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Changchun, capital of Northeast
China's Jilin Province, has been making pains-taking efforts to
build a strong backing for use of more overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The strong backing will be realized through establishing a
special committee on use of overseas investment, with the city's
top party or government leaders as the head, a data base on
project information, as well as an efficient management system,
said Li Shu, Mayor of the city.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, Changchun, where China's First
Automobile Works (FAW) is located, has made a use of 900 million
U.S. dollars of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
During the period, 292 old industrial enterprises have been
upgraded with the aid of overseas investment and have been showing
better efficiency with the inflow of sophisticated technologies
and advanced management expertise.
</P>
<P>
Total industrial output value generated by overseas-financed
businesses in the city's total industrial output value has also
increased from 3.62 percent to 25 percent in the past five years.
</P>
</TEXT>
