<HEADLINE> Grant Retains WBO Middleweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Otis Grant, who took eight
stitches over his left eye after a head butt, regained his WBO
middleweight title by stopping fellow American Ernesto Sena in the
ninth round Tuesday night in Kanata, Ontario.
</P>
<P>
Referee Mark Nelson stopped Grant's first title defense at 1:57
of the ninth round of the scheduled 12-rounder, ruling the cut
from the previous round was in a dangerous location.
</P>
<P>
Grant was ahead on the cards of all three judges when the fight
was stopped.
</P>
<P>
Grant improved to 31-1-1 with 17 knockouts, while Sena dropped
to 34-10-3 with 10 knockouts. 
