<HEADLINE> Direct Flights to Start Between Kathmandu, Vienna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 13 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian Airlines will
operate direct flights between Kathmandu and Vienna on September
24, The Rising Nepal reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We will be operating one flight every week all the year round
and two flights a week in October and November which is the peak
tourist season for Nepal," Robert Stainoch, country manager of the
airlines for India, Nepal and Sri Lanka, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The airlines is planning to operate two flights every week all
the year round from the winter of 1999, he said.
</P>
<P>
The airlines, the national flag carrier of Austria, is the
first airlines to operate direct flights between Kathmandu and a
city in the European Continent, and it will be using Airbus A310
for the flight, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Stainoch said the direct flight is expected to bring in 5,000
European tourists to Nepal in the first three months of its
operation.
</P>
<P>
Nepal's tourism industry suffered a setback after Lufthansa of
Germany pulled out about a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The limited seat capacity of the Royal Nepal Airlines has been
a major constraint for bringing in more tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Visit Nepal Year'98 is believed to have paved the way for
international airlines to operate flights to the Himalayan
kingdom, the daily said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
