<HEADLINE> Thailand's Muan Chon Party to Merge With NAP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Muan Chon Party (Mass
Party) has decided to dissolve and merge with the New Aspiration
Party (NAP).
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at the party's general assembly on May
10, according to a report here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The party's leader Chalerm Yubamrung and the party's other MP,
Araya Chumduang, went to NAP office Tuesday to apply for
membership, the report said. The party has only two MPs in the
House of Representatives.
</P>
