<HEADLINE> New Zealand Recalls Envoy from India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, May 13 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand has recalled its
high commissioner from New Delhi as a protest to India's
resumption of nuclear tests, newspaper The Dominion reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand high commissioner in New Delhi has been told to fly
home on the first available plane, while the parliament passed a
resolution condemning the tests.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Prime Minister Jenny Shipley as saying that
the government wants to send the strongest message to India over
its move to resume the tests.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Foreign Minister Don McKinnon called the tests "a
gross insult" to the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
The opposition parties also backed the government response to
India. 
</P>
