<HEADLINE> Collapsing Scaffold Kills Six </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- A scaffold collapsed at a
construction site in this capital city of southwest China's Yunnan
Province and killed six workers yesterday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said that the scaffold collapsed at 2:40 p.m. when
six workers were fixing it. Five died on the spot and one died
later in hospital.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua was told that the cause for the accident was that the
handing scaffold was too heavy.
</P>
<P>
The six victims of the incident were involved in putting up the
20-story main building of the Yunnan Communications Hospital.
</P>
