<HEADLINE> Australia Considers 2010 World Cup Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Australia is considering a bid to
host the 2010 World Cup finals, Soccer Australia chairman David
Hill said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are exploring the possibility ... but it would have to have
the support of the federal and state governments," Hill told the
Australian Associated Press (AAP).
</P>
<P>
Hill said Australia was also looking at the possibility of
hosting the Confederations Cup which is played every two years
between the various continental champions. 
