<HEADLINE> Railway Company Listed on Shanghai Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 13 (Xinhua) -- China's first A-share issued by
the country's railway sector was listed on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange this week.
</P>
<P>
Tielong Industrial Stock Company, whose shareholder is Dalian
Railway Co. Ltd. in northeast China's Liaoning Province, issued 25
million A-shares (shares issued to domestic investors) on
Monday. On its first day of trading, each Tielong share sold at 25
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Tielong, with a total of 95.388 million capital shares, will
use the raised funds on the construction of railway infrastructure
facilities and the development of high technology, according to
company officials.
</P>
<P>
The company, with nine subsidiaries and branches, took the lead
in China's railway sector in introducing a shareholding system as
early as five years ago. The company's business includes
transportation, storage, industrial production, catering services
and tourism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
