<HEADLINE> Roncero Heads Spanish Squad for Euro Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Fabian Roncero, the winner of last
month's Rotterdam Marathon, will lead the Spanish marathon squad
to European championships in August, the Spanish athletics
federation announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Spanish runners made a clean sweep of the medals at the last
European championships in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Roncero holds the fastest marathon time of the year with two
hours seven minutes and 26 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Also in the squad are Tokyo Marathon winner Alberto Juzdado and
Abel Anton, the 1997 world champion and London Marathon winner
last month. 
</P>
