<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Kills 12 People in Indonesian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people died and nine others
were wounded when a fire gutted a three-story shop/house in Duta
Harapan Indah, Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, Tuesday, police
here confirmed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Eleven of the victims died after being trapped by the flames,
and another victim broke her neck after jumping from the third
floor of the building to escape the flames, said the police.
</P>
<P>
All the victims were employees of a private garment producer,
who worked and lived in the shop/house.
</P>
<P>
The fire started at 3 a.m. local time. Initial reports
suggested it was ignited by an electric short circuit on the first
floor of the building which did not have any fire exits.
</P>
<P>
The fire then spread to the second floor, where employees were
sleeping after finishing work on the night shift.
</P>
<P>
Three fire engines were dispatched to the scene. The blaze was
brought under control in two hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
