<DOCNO> XIE19980513.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile Condemns Indian Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean government has
condemned India for its recent nuclear tests, describing it as an
unnecessary threat to international peace and security.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean foreign ministry said in a communique that the
tests had severely damaged the nuclear test ban treaty, which is
supported by the majority of the international community and is
struggling to come into force.
</P>
<P>
With the tests, New Delhi had violated the agreements on
promotion of nuclear disarmament, the communique said. The
agreements were adopted at the Ninth Summit of the Non-Aligned
States held in Colombia.
</P>
<P>
India, a founding member of the non-aligned movement, set off
three nuclear devices and tested a short-range Trident missile on
Monday. The tests have triggered worldwide protests, including
from the United States, which is considering sanctions against
India.
</P>
<P>
The communique also reaffirmed Chilean opposition to nuclear
tests and to any country breaking the nuclear test ban. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
