<HEADLINE> Highlights of Beijing-based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Senior Chinese officials attended a lecture yesterday on
financial security and improvement of the legal system in the
financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Senior leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Hu Jintao, Wei
Jianxing and Li Lanqing along with Communist Party and government
officials were present at a lecture given by Cao Jianming, a
professor of political science and law with the East China College.
</P>
<P>
-- A latest report from the Customs shows that China's foreign
trade volume reached 97.48 billion US dollars in the first four
months this year, up 7.9 percent from the year-ago period. Last
year's year-on-year growth was 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese scientists discovered a 1,727-meter-thick oil
bearing layer in northwest part of the Qaidam Basin on the
Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China is willing to continue its friendly exchanges and
mutually beneficial cooperation oriented toward the 21st century
with Bulgaria on the basis of mutual respect, mutual benefit and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, pledged Li Peng
in a meeting yesterday with visiting Bulgarian President Petar
Stoyanov.
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting yesterday with former
U.S. Secretary of State Cyrus Vance, called President Clinton's
June China visit a major event in Sino-U.S. relationship.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the visit will enable the two
countries to make new progress in their relationship.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese government and people are delighted to see that
the Thai economy is recovering, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- Higher learning institutions across China are required to
offer a course on Deng Xiaoping Theory starting this year,
according to a notice issued yesterday by the Ministry of
Education and the Department of Publicity of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
