<HEADLINE> Policeman Killed in Kosovo Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 12 (Xinhua) -- One policeman died and two others
were seriously injured in an attack by armed ethnic Albanians in
Yugoslavia's troubled Serbian province of Kosovo on Tuesday, the
Yugoslavian Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Albanians attacked the police near a town in Oranovac area
around 11:00 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
The injured policemen were immediately sent to the Pristina
medical center in the capital of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The police are today still pursuing for those responsible.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo was plunged into chaos in February when ethnic Albanian
separatists intensified their campaign for the independence of the
province, where ethnic Albanians account for 90 percent of the
population. 
