<HEADLINE> New Ukrainian Soviet Holds First Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The newly elected Supreme Soviet of
Ukraine, the national legislature, held its first plenary session
Tuesday, formally beginning its four-year term.
</P>
<P>
A five-member interim presidium was elected to preside over the
meeting until the new chairman is chosen.
</P>
<P>
Nominations for chairman will open from May 14. Since the
parliament is divided into eight party-affiliated groups and each
has its own man for chairmanship, competition and bargaining
before voting are expected to be fierce.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma made a state of the nation
address to the 450-seat congress on Tuesday morning. Also present
at the session were cabinet members headed by Prime Minister
Valery Pustovoitenko.
</P>
<P>
Only 435 legislators were officially recognized. The rest were
still vacant on Monday night either because ballots have to be
recast in several constituencies or the qualifications of some
congressmen elected are still under evaluation by the central
election committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
