<HEADLINE> Duncan, Van Horn Top NBA Rookie Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Rookie of the Year Tim Duncan of
the San Antonio Spurs and Keith Van Horn of the New Jersey Nets
were unanimously voted to the NBA's All-Rookie team, the league
announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Guard Brevin Knight and center Zydrunas Ilgauskas of the
Cleveland Cavaliers and guard-forward Ron Mercer of the Boston
Celtics rounded out the first team.
</P>
<P>
Duncan and Van Horn received the maximum 56 points in balloting
by the NBA's 29 head coaches, who were not allowed to vote for
their own players. The two forwards were named on each of the
ballots, with two points for first place and one for second place.
</P>
<P>
Knight received 54 points and was named on 26 first-place
ballots, while Ilgauskas had 51 points with 25-first-team
votes. Mercer had 23 votes for first and a total of 50 points.
</P>
<P>
The second team included three forwards -- Cleveland's Cedric
Henderson, Philadelphia's Tim Thomas and the Los Angeles Clippers'
Maurice Taylor -- and two guards -- the Cavaliers' Derek Anderson
and Denver's Bobby Jackson. 
</P>
