<HEADLINE> Indonesia Needs to Import Rice This Year: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia needs to import a
significant amount of rice to meet this year's demand for the
commodity, a government official said.
</P>
<P>
Head of the National Logistics Agency Beddu Amang said here
Tuesday that it will be difficult for Indonesia to regain
self-sufficiency in rice in the near future, Antara News Agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The country has been hit by a long drought, some rice
producing areas are suffering from disease and insect and pest
attacks, while many rice fields have now been turned into
residential or industrial areas," he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1984, Indonesia managed to become self-sufficient in rice
after many years of being the largest importer in the world.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia imported one million ton of rice last year. 
</P>
