<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Economy Increasing Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 13 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Province in east China
witnessed its steady economic increase in the first four months of
1998, according to the latest figures from the provincial
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that the province's industrial output value
during the period amounted to 268.3 billion yuan, increasing by 10
percent over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The production to marketing ratio also reaches 94.1 percent,
equal to that of the same period of last year, according to the
bureau's report.
</P>
<P>
And the ratio of sectors of high-technology, electronics,
medicine and machinery are beyond 95 percent.
</P>
<P>
One of China's major industrial provinces, Jiangsu has
eliminated its control over the markets of production materials
and consumption, except for five industrial products including
coal and oil.
</P>
<P>
The province's joint-ventures are also on sound track, said an
official of the statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that the foreign-funded enterprises, whose
annual sales volume exceeding five million yuan each, finished
industrial output of 53.8 billion yuan during the first four
months this year, a year-on-year increase of 23.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
