<HEADLINE> Former Colombian Defense Minister Assassinated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Former Colombian defense
minister, retired General Fernado Landazabal Reyes, was shot dead
by three gunmen in the street here on Tuesday, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
Argemiro Serna, commander of the police of Santa Fe de Bogota,
said the ex-minister was killed while walking along the street to
his office. He was shot three times in the head and his body was
riddled with bullets.
</P>
<P>
Reyes was defense minister and commander of the national army
during the administration of President Belisario Betancourt
Cuartas in 1982-1986. He resigned later when his strict policy
against guerillas was repeatedly criticized by others.
</P>
<P>
The independent presidential candidate Noemi Sanin said the
assassination is probably a reprisal between right and left
wingers.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Alfonzo Lopez Caballero described the
accident as a "horrible crime" and added, "it would seem that a
dirty war is escalating in Colombia."
</P>
<P>
In recent months, two human rights activists were also
assassinated in Colombia, and both were from the political left
wing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
