<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Andean Corporation of
Development (CAF) is issuing bonds worth 150 million U.S. dollars
in the European market as of Tuesday; it is the second such
issuance this year.
</P>
<P>
The executive president of the CAF, Enrique Garcia, said
Tuesday the issuance is in response to a diversification strategy
of the institution, oriented to maintain a continuous presence in
Europe which will introduce a single currency in January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
