<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Missile Defense System Test Fails Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Pentagon's fifth missile
defense system failed to intercept a target on Tuesday, the
Defense Department said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The test on the Theater High-Altitude Area Defense, or THAAD
system, was done at White Sands Missile Range, New Mexico. The
missile, built by Lockhead Martin Corp., lost control shortly
after launch, the statement said. It appeared to be caused by a
booster rocket problem.
</P>
<P>
The missile hit the missile range about three kilometers north
of the launch site. The interceptor missile and target debris
landed on the missile range, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The test at 7:20 a.m. EDT was the eighth overall for the THAAD
and the fifth involving an actual missile flight and attempted
intercept.
</P>
<P>
The THAAD system is designed to provide U.S. forces in the
field protection from attack by Scud and other short- and
medium-range missiles. It is to provide broader defensive coverage
than the Patriot missile system.
</P>
<P>
The program, emerging from former U.S. President Ronald
Reagon's "Star War" plan 15 years ago, was to be deployed in three
years if necessary.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980513.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> DPRK Calls on Japan to Be Sincere in Talks on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) Tuesday called on Japan to be sincere in meeting its
promise to normalize relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK General Delegate in France and Extraordinary and
Plenipotentiary Ambassador to the UNESCO, Ri Tae Gyun, said at a
press briefing here that the normalization of relations between
the DPRK and Japan conforms with the wishes of the people of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
But despite the efforts made by the DPRK side and because of
the non-confidence stand maintained by Tokyo, the bilateral talks
by officials of foreign ministries of the two countries held in
Beijing since last year have been stalled for eight months, said
Ri.
</P>
<P>
Ri recalled that the Korean Labor Party and three major parties
of Japan reached an agreement in 1995 in Pyongyang on launching
the process of normalization of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK side holds that the talks on normalization of
relations should be held without pre-condition, but the Japanese
side has posed pre-condition for moving forward the talks, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The high personalities of Tokyo based their excuses for
suspending the talks on "fictive" stories without any witness to
support them, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ri said despite the tremendous sufferings inflicted upon the
Korean people by Japan during the colonial rule in the early half
of this century, DPRK is willing to turn a page of history and
renew its relations with Japan.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that during the Japanese colonial rule, six million
Korean men were kidnapped by Japanese imperialists to carry out
slave labors, 200,000 Korean women were enslaved as comfort women
by the Japanese imperial army, and one million Koreans were
massacred by the Japanese imperialists.
</P>
<P>
So far the Japanese government has not made any excuse for
these atrocities and instead ridiculously presented fictive
stories in which Japan posed itself as the victim, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
