<HEADLINE> New Kimberley Mines Discovered in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Angola's National Diamond-Mining
Corporation and South Africa's De Beers Angola Prospecting have
discovered two new Kimberley mines in the northeast of Angola,
with rich reserves.
</P>
<P>
A joint communique issued here Tuesday by the two companies
said this is the first Kimberley mines discovered since Angola's
independence in 1975.
</P>
<P>
The new mines, said the communique, are located to the north
of Saurimo, capital city of Lunda-Sul Province near the
diamond-rich mine of Catoca.
</P>
<P>
The two companies started their cooperation in June 1996.
Lunda-Sul is one of the three regions they are approved of
exploitation under the rules of Angolan government.
</P>
<P>
The two companies have reported the news of discovery to the
Ministry of Geology and Mines and submit the samples of the
mineral to De Beers' geological science laboratory in
Johannesburg for test.
</P>
<P>
In early 1970's, the communique said, De Beers found over 120
Kimberley mines in various parts of Angola. However, due to
certain regulations at that time, the company did not mine the
reserves and evacuated from the mines. Enditme

NNNN
00:25 00:25 g # PAB
</P>
