<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Tourism Sector Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's fast-growing tourism
sector is expected to earn about 300 million U.S. Dollars this
year, an increase of 100 million Dollars from last year, chief
executive of Zimbabwe Tourism Authority Joe Chigwedere said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chigwedere attributed this development to growing recognition
of Zimbabwe as a favorite tourist destination in the southern
African region.
</P>
<P>
"Zimbabwe is being recognised as a favorite destination with
more to offer than other places in the region," he told the
Zimbabwe News Agency.
</P>
<P>
He said the sector's publicity and marketing campaigns were
leading to increased interest in the country.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that Zimbabwe has experienced a steady
growth in the tourism sector with the number of arrivals
increasing from 1.4 million in 1995 to 1.7 million in 1996 and
1.9 million last year. 
</P>
