<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Makes Strides on AIDS Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Gordon Chavhunduka, president of
the Zimbabwean National Traditional Healers Association, said
Tuesday that the organisation has identified medicines that are
likely to remove some or all the symptoms associated with AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Addressing delegates attending the AIDS exposition in Harare,
the president said medicines used by his members on AIDS patients
were analyzed by a research institute in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Identification and isolation of pure compounds from some of
the plants that were active against HIV/AIDS had been done.
</P>
<P>
However, the question of ownership of the compound or drug had
become a deterring issue as rich opportunists would want to
capitalize on that.
</P>
<P>
He added that discoveries which had been made could be
patented should funds become available.
</P>
<P>
The association has 50,000 practising healers. 
</P>
