<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Commander in S. Leone Promoted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Colonel Maxwell Khobe, a Nigerian
and commander of the west African peace-keeping force ECOMOG's
operation in Sierra Leone, has been promoted to the rank of
brigadier-general.
</P>
<P>
The official News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) Tuesday quoted a
statement of the ECOMOG headquarters in Liberia as saying that
the approval of Khobe's promotion by Nigerian Head of State
General Sani Abacha, was in recognition of his courage and
excellent performance during the operation that flushed out the
military junta in Freetown led by Major Paul Johnny Koromah.
</P>
