<HEADLINE> Sudan, U.N. Agency Sign Health Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Sudan and the United Nations
Population Fund signed an agreement here on Tuesday on health
cooperation, the Sudanese News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the U.N. agency will grant Sudan 658,000
dollars to finance the construction of 25 medical centers in 16
provinces in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will be carried out in early June, is aimed
at helping the refugees driven to the provinces by the civil war
in southern Sudan, desertification and aridity.
</P>
<P>
The rebels have been fighting Sudanese government since 1983
for autonomy in the south, which is maily Christian and animist.
</P>
<P>
During the signing ceremony, Sudanese Minister of Social
Planning El-Tayeb Ibrahim Mohamed Kheir voiced hope that the
U.N. agency would help Sudan to attain its strategic goals.
</P>
<P>
Sudan is managing to fight poverty, solve the problem of
homelessness and try to meet the needs of orphans, widows and
others in difficulty, according to the news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese official called for support from domestic and
foreign humanitarian organizations to solve Sudan's problems.
</P>
