<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE to Buy 80 U.S. F-16 Fighters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates will
buy up to 80 U.S.-made F-16 fighter jets in a deal worth about 6
billion dollars, the UAE's crown prince and U.S. Vice President Al
Gore said in a statement after White House talks Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After the talks with UAE Crown Prince Sheik Khalifa bin Zayed
Al Nahyan, Gore said the United States was setting the seal on a
strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
"For both countries, it opens the door to enhanced cooperation
and training and operations. This will give our forces a
tremendous advantage in preserving the security and stability of
the Gulf region to which we are firmly committed," Gore said.
</P>
<P>
Gore plans to travel to Texas Friday to tour the Lockheed
Martin plant in Fort Worth, where the F-16 is assembled. "This
deal is good news for the American economy," he said. 
</P>
