<HEADLINE> Britain Expresses Concern Over Kosovo Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook
Tuesday expressed deepening concern over the worsening situation
in Kosovo, the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at British parliament Tuesday afternoon, Cook
said, "The situation in Kosovo continues to be a matter of
deepening concern. Fatalities in Kosovo are now an almost daily
occurrence."
</P>
<P>
Cook, whose country is the current EU president, urged the
Yugoslav government leaders to accept responsibility for failing
to hold political negotiations with ethnic Albanians in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"There can be no question of us accepting the Federal Republic
as part of the family of modern Europe unless Belgrade stops its
present repression and starts to accept the principles of human
rights," he said.
</P>
<P>
At a London meeting of the G-8 foreign ministers last week, an
investment ban was imposed upon the Belgrade government, which was
blamed for failing to open political dialogue with Kosovan ethnic
leaders. 
