<HEADLINE> UK to Build National Library for Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A National Library for Women was
launched in Britain Tuesday to celebrate the contribution which
women made to society, said media reports Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 4.2 million pounds (6.9 million U.S.
dollars) of money from Britain's national lottery was granted to
the building of the library and a further 2.65 million pounds (4.4
million dollars) needs to be raised.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts said that the move is an expensive gesture to
political correctness.
</P>
<P>
"The library will acknowledge, celebrate and record for all
time the actions of women pioneers, the many thousands who have
made no less high profile contributions and those in the
generations to come," said Barbara Follett, a Labor MP who is in
charge of the fund raising.
</P>
<P>
The library will be situated in east London, and will contain
material on the suffragette campaign at the turn of the century to
win the right of women to vote as well as first editions of works
by influential women writers. 
</P>
