<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays Credits for Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday three interest-free credits totaling 44 million U.S.
dollars to help Albania finance two development projects.
</P>
<P>
The first credit of 17 million dollars is provided to assist
the country in its transport infrastructure construction at the
Port of Durres.
</P>
<P>
This project will improve the efficiency and capacity of the
Port of Durres by increasing its commercial orientation through
the establishment of an autonomous port authority, privatization
of port operations, improvement of Customs procedures, operations
and safety as well as rehabilitating port infrastructure to
accommodate anticipated traffic demand and attract transit
traffic.
</P>
<P>
The second credit of 17 million dollars equivalent is earmarked
for the country's health system recovery and development project.
The project will establish and strengthen Albania's health sector,
and improve the accessibility, quality and efficiency of essential
health services.
</P>
<P>
The third credit of some 10 million dollars equivalent will be
used to finance its urban land management project. This project
will provide essential urban infrastructure to unserved or
neglected areas in Tirana and surrounding areas. It will also
strengthen the institution responsible for delivery of urban
services at the national and local levels.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be provided through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional
lending wing for developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Since joining the IDA in 1991, IDA commitments to Albania total
approximately 313 million dollars for 25 projects, excluding those
three approved Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
