<HEADLINE> Yahoo! Premieres On-Line Movie Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Yahoo! Inc, the world-famous
provider of Internet search engine, now is providing movies for
its millions of users.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo! Inc. Tuesday announced the release of Yahoo! Movies
(http://movies.yahoo.com ). This new site packages a
comprehensive directory of compelling movie and entertainment
information, including local showtimes, into one easy-to-use
location.
</P>
<P>
Offering movie-goers the latest movie-related content and
resources, Yahoo! Movies also features upcoming movie releases,
top box office movie information, news and reviews, net events, an
actor index and movie matches. The site also provides a number of
features to help users make informed viewing decisions.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo! Movies joins other members of the Yahoo! entertainment
cast including Yahoo! Games, Yahoo! TV Coverage and Yahoo! Comics.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo! Inc has been making big strides into the worldwide
network, already having set up sites in 11 different languages:
Danish, English, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean,
Norwegian, Portuguese, Spanish and Swedish.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo!'s global network of properties served an average of 95
million page views per day during the month of March and continues
to have the largest audience of any on-line service or site on the
Web with more than 30 million unique U.S. adult users per month.
</P>
<P>
Yahoo! Inc. now offers a network of branded Web programming
serving millions of users daily. 
</P>
