<HEADLINE> N.Y. Stocks Advanced Toward Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks closed higher
Tuesday after seesawing through the day, rallying to approach its
record high in the final hour as interest rates sank in the bond
market.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 70.25 points to
9,161.77. It's just 30 points below last Monday's record finish
at 9,192.66.
</P>
<P>
Decliners still outnumbered advancers by a 9-to-8 margin on
active volume which totaled 600.90 million shares, up from 556.97
million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
